  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators have developed a novel instrument for taking endometrial biopsies at no
      touch (vaginoscopic) hysterectomy which avoids the need to instrument the vagina with
      speculums and tenaculums, and also avoids the possible need for cervical dilatation. The
      investigators wish to study the ease of use and efficacy of the new device compared with
      traditional techniques of endometrial sampling at hysteroscopy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We have developed a novel instrument for taking endometrial biopsies at no touch
      (vaginoscopic) hysterectomy which avoids the need to instrument the vagina with speculums and
      tenaculums, and also avoids the possible need for cervical dilatation. We wish to study the
      ease of use and efficacy of the new device compared with traditional techniques of
      endometrial sampling at hysteroscopy in terms of biopsy adequacy, the time taken to obtain a
      biopsy and patient experience.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
